updated_cases.title: Verify swg-api-service process bulk URL lookup requests and verify the presence of rate limit-related headers in the API response.
updated_cases.custom_summary: Verify swg-api-service process bulk URL lookup requests and verify the presence of rate limit-related headers in the API response.
updated_cases.custom_steps: Send multiple bulk URL lookup requests to the /api/v2/nsiq/url-lookup endpoint
updated_cases.custom_expected:
The API response should include headers such as X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, and X-RateLimit-Reset, providing information about the rate limit status.
Response includes guidance on the remaining quota and the reset time for the tenant.

updated_cases.title: Verify swg-api-service handle bulk URL lookup request exceeding Rate Limit (daily quota) for a tenant
updated_cases.custom_summary: Verify swg-api-service handle bulk URL lookup request exceeding Rate Limit (daily quota) for a tenant
updated_cases.custom_steps: Send multiple bulk URL lookup requests to the /api/v2/nsiq/url-lookup endpoint
updated_cases.custom_expected:
Response status code 429 Too Many Requests
Rate limit headers (X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset) are correctly populated in the response headers.
Show header no matter what
Response includes appropriate error message indicating that the rate limit has been exceeded.
